			<div id="Q1">
				<h4>What is Omegrep?</h4>
				<p>Omegrep helps you find interesting chat logs from <a href="http://www.omegle.com" target="_blank">Omegle.com</a>.</p>
			</div>
			<div id="Q2">
				<h4>Omegle? What's that?</h4>
				<p>From <a href="http://www.omegle.com" target="_blank">Omegle's website</a>: "Omegle is a great way of meeting new friends. When you use Omegle, we pick another user at random and let you have a one-on-one chat with each other. Chats are completely anonymous, and you can disconnect whenever you like."</p>
			</div>
			<div id="Q3">
				<h4>Are you affiliated with Omegle?</h4>
				<p>Omegrep is <strong>not</strong> affiliated with Omegle in any way.</p>
			</div>
			<div id="Q4">
				<h4>How did you get these chat logs?</h4>
				<p>All saved logs are publicly available on Omegle.com. Simply visit logs.omegle.com/#####, replacing ##### with any 5, 6 or 7 digit hexadecimal number. Some numbers will give you a 403 error, but most will not. Here is an <a href="http://logs.omegle.com/f7b7344" target="_blank">example</a>.</p>
			</div>
			<div id="Q5">
				<h4>Why isn't my chat log showing up in search?</h4>
				<p>Theres a lot of logs out there, so unfortunately it may take us some time to get to yours. We have plans to add the ability to "submit" a chat log. <a href="mailto:hello@omegrep.com">Send us an email</a> to hurry us up if you'd be interested in that.</p>
			</div>
			<div id="Q6">
				<h4>Why is the text in search results wrong sometimes?</h4>
				<p>Omegle saves logs as images, so we have to get the computer to "read" the images into text files. Reading screenshots is hard for computers, and sometimes he makes mistakes. Please forgive him!</p>
			</div>
			<div id="Q7">
				<h4>Why did you create this?</h4>
