			<div id="Q8">
				<h4>Did you "hack" Omegle?</h4>
				<p>We did not hack Omegle. All the information used on this website is publicly available on Omegle.com. We simply organized it. See Question 3 for more details.</p>
			</div>
			<div id="Q9">
				<h4>How do I get a chat log removed?</h4>
				<p>If you find a chat log containing your personal information, or links to to something illegal or horrific, let us know via <a href="mailto:hello@omegrep.com">email</a> or the report button and we will remove it ASAP. Unfortunately, removing it from here does not remove it from Omegle's servers, so we'd recommend contacting Omegle, and generally not giving your personal information to strangers on the internet.</p>
			</div>
			<div id="Q10">
				<h4>What does Omegrep's name mean?</h4>
				<p>Omegrep is a combination of "Omegle" and "<a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grep" target="_blank">grep</a>", a command line utility used for searching through text.</p>
